It doesn’t matter how good the food is when the restaurant isn’t clean and the owner isn’t honest.  Apparently he recognized we were tourists because he uncharged on everything to the point where we were completely shocked at the price if a simple dinner....  the portions were small, food was missing and the owner was rude.  What was worse was that we knew we had made a mistake when we walked in and saw how dirty it was...  the bathrooms were disgustingly filthy and the restaurant wasn’t air conditioned, hopefully the ac was just broken because it was stifling in there....

The best thing about this falafel place is the pita.  It’s thick and soft and heavy, unlike a lot of places that use thin, dry pita.  I’ve been going here for years and it’s usually great, but the last time I was in town it just wasn’t up to par.  Our food didn’t taste that fresh and the restaurant itself had a pretty rank smell inside.  I’ll still go back in the future, especially for a super late night meal; hopefully this latest trip was just a fluke.
The food and prices are great, but it's never open at 10 am like Google suggests
Everything on the Gyro was so fresh and the customer service was great. I like how he repeated my order back to me to make sure everything was correct.
I love this place, after the bars we stop by here for a bite to eat ♥️♥️♥️
chicken sandwich was quite serious

This place simply has THE BEST tzatziki in the world.  Casual Middle Eastern fare that's absolutely delicious. Service is awesome. Have the tzatziki!

Legendary guy with lots of experience that you need to ask him about! We had a cool conversation and the food was tasty as well. Falafel was fresh and soft - not dry as in other places. Would recommend.

4/19 I'm adding an edit, here, and I'm hoping the restaurant takes notice: The food is really really good. I returned recently and my companion declared the gyro the best he'd ever had. I'm still in love with the spanikopita.  As noted in other reviews, though, the prices on the menu  are not what you're charged at checkout, and that's not OK.  I'm in love with the spanakopita, apparently on the menu as 'spinach samosa.'  The first time I happened upon this place I'd asked about the spinach wrap, but they were out and he suggested this instead.  Little triangular spinach pies, with flakey phyllo outside and a light almost mousse of spinach and sauce inside. OMG.  Especially dipped into the home made hummus and tzatziki*.  Great reviews from companions of the DC platter and the Chicken Gyro as well.   I've also had the baklava and another dessert, and was quite happy with them.  DC cafe is open late, to 1a on weeknights and apparently later on weekends.  He seems to make everything when ordered so it's not immediately out, but if you're eating in he'll bring it to the table.  Cash is better than card; there's an ATM outside.  * again, not what I think of as tzatziki - far thicker and perfectly tangy.  I wasn't sure what it was until I asked, but I wanted to eat every bit.

DC cafe is a must. It's the only place in DC that you may find open and offering great tasting food after 3am. Love their lamb gyros and baklava. The service is not conventional and offering fake smiles, but they do care a great deal about their customers. The owner used to extend the hours when I arrived late at 4am couple of times.
A D.C. must! Unpretentious setting and delicious, inexpensive food. Glad we stopped in.
Extremely cold in this place it really overshadowed any thoughts I could have for this place.
Great options for people with dietary restrictions and great customer service!
This is hands down the best shawarma I have ever had. Owner is friendly and the food was prepared quickly. Popped with flavor and spices.
Always a great experience at DC Cafe. The food is good and delicious. Nice service. It stays open late so it's perfect for those late nite hunger binges.
Delicious

Best late night gyros and shawarma. Perfect for 12 pm or 12 am.
Absolutely delish!  Stopped in for dinner.  I ordered the DC Platter.   The owner was such a sweet man to chat with and very accommodating to my substitution requests.

Great food and open late!  DC Cafe is always a great go-to when your flight gets you downtown after hours, but you still want some real food. The hummus is excellent. Tip: try to bring cash if you can, but they do take cards with a small fee.

I travel to DC often but this was the first time staying in the Dupont Circle neighborhood.  I make a point to visit family owned businesses whenever I travel.  DC Cafe is run by the nicest guy who makes some of the best Mediterranean food I've had.  If you're ever in the area, I recommend you try it.  I will go back for lunch every time I go to DC whether I'm near Dupont Circle or I have to take the Metro to get there.  It's that good.
The food was delicious and the proprietor is very nice!
Great little place to eat, all day and late night. Been around for over 30 years! Simple, tasty and comfortable. Highly recommended for a quick bite!
What the DC Cafe lacks in atmosphere it more than makes up for with quality. I tried both the shish tawook and the chicken shawerma and they were delicious.

I have lived all over Europe and Turkey and this is, hands down, the most authentic Levantine lamb pita you will have outside of Syria or Lebanon. I walked by at midnight on a Friday and wasn't sure if it was open but the owner/cook was outside and said yes we're open and I went in and I asked him if I was going to get Greek or Turkish style and he said he and I got no kidding the best Levantine seasoned lamb pita I had had in probably 15 or 20 years. There was no discussion of how late it was or how much business had come through it was basically a discussion of the history of the past of the area where he had come from and how fantastic the food was and it was awesome. I will be eating here every single day every single time I am in this part of DC. If you are missing the Dinner of Germany and Turkey or the Gyro of Greece, you must eat here.

Excellent. Ordered the Lebanese platter and every single item on my plate was richly flavored. The owner/chef is a master! The menu features some items that are hard to find at local middle eastern places and they're well worth trying. If the classics are more your thing, they too are top notch. Even the basics like the rice and salad -- stuff that is all too often bland and boring -- really shine here.
Rather go to a restaurant. 2 lamb gyros and 2 sodas and small fries cost us $30. That’s insane.

This is always a go-to place because the food is good. Not much to say on the outside but the owner is really nice and they take real good care of you. I always get the combination chicken and lamb with the hot sauce and it's always on point. The gyros are also good.
Great food. Always go there when I'm in the area
Quality fresh food and a nice owner.
Best gyro plate in DC. I sometimes drive from Laurel MD to get a platter to take back home.
Awesome food!
Lamb gyro was excellent.
Delicious!! Thanks for being open so late

Best place to visit after a night of bar hopping. Owner/chef of the restaurant is the nicest guy on the planet. You can tell he’s passionate about his business. Gyros are THE BEST. Love this place and will always recommend to friends who bar hop around DuPont
The food here is amazing and fresh!.  Will highly recommend this place.  Great cook, great food!!!.

This review is strictly for their customer service. I ordered the baba ganouj which was listed on their menu and on the walls for $6.99. The old guy who prepared my food asked if I wanted an extra pita bread (assuming that it's free? or probably should cost less than $1), so I said yes. The order comes with only 1 pita by the way.  So as I was ready to pay, he said it was $9.99. I was confused. Why is it so much?  $3 more is a bit much for a DC Tax (5.57%). And no where it stated that there's minimum for a credit card either. So I asked him why is it $9.99 instead of $6.99? Without any proof he said because he gave me an extra pita (lie #1) and tax (lie #2). What a shady business and worse terrible  business ethic! Lesson to learn -- if you must go to this place to eat, make sure you have cash handy and confirm the price as listed on their menu before you pay for your food. This place truly left a bad taste in mouth.
Best beef and lamb gyro I've had! Very casual spot just a few blocks from Dupont Circle.
Amazing I like so much  ilove flafelll
Tastiest gyro and chicken sandwich/platter ever! Authentic food and service. Highly recommended.
Quite possibly the worst Mediterranean food I have ever had.  The meats were dry, the falafel was overcooked, and just about everything lacked flavor, including the rice.

Stop for a bit and chat with the owner! Great guy - very entertaining.

I wanted to like this place so much. It's hot and dirty, feels like you're in Baghdad.  Ordered combo plate and the chicken was tender and delicious, rice was great, beef burnt and hard, pitta or naan was heated on griddle in rancid oil. It you know what that smells like and how bad it is for you I'm sure you understand my experience. I also ordered the Lebanese salad, I watched it being made, the guy was picking out rotting lettuce as he attempted to make it. He should have thrown the whole thing out! And the falafel was fried in rancid oil, over fried until it was hard to bite into!
I enjoyed every.single.bite. The Chicken Gyro platter was soo good and he made it specially spicy for me.

Been eating here since I was 18 and the food and the chicken isn't the freshest mom and pop spot. Sometimes if you watch you will see rants and nice run around. I stopped by last week around 10 on food was horrible. Chicken gyro was stale and the baklava was old I paid for two orders only got one. Spent about 21 bucks and it was a waste.

Recently, I visited DC Cafe while traveling through Washington DC.  The food was delicious, especially the lamb and hummus; the prices were reasonable, especially for the DC area; and the owner was friendly and attentive.  I highly recommend this establishment.

I don't usually write reviews but this was hands down the best Gyro I've ever had. I'm serious....I was sitting in my hotel room, after ordering our food and having some great conversation with the owner, and I bit into the Gyro and said "Holy $#&@" to my wife. The gyro had lasting and vibrant flavor from every single bite. It's not the dry/ flavorless meat that can happen easily on Gyros. You'd expect this quality of food from an exquisite restaurant. The meat was savory, tender, and delicious! Highly recommend!

The food is delicious and exactly what you might expect from a small, local cafe.  I highly recommend the DC Cafe for its service and incredible kindness of the owners. I participated in an urban plunge project in which I and a few other students lived as homeless individuals in the DC community. The people of this cafe were some of the few who treated us with genuine compassion and responded to our appeals for help.  I encourage everyone to support his local, small business.

Hole in the wall -- nothing fancy, but some of their dishes are very, very good. I've found myself craving their falafel and some of their combo dishes. Also a nice place to sit outside and people watch.
